# Executive Overview

VELOX X-1 is a conceptual human-powered mobility system intended to augment bicycle propulsion through temporary storage and controlled release of mechanically generated energy.

Unlike electric bicycles that rely on batteries and electric motors, the VELOX X-1 concept proposes:

* Human-powered energy generation
* Hydraulic compression storage
* Pneumatic energy buffering
* Controlled rotational torque release
* Regenerative pressure recovery

The central objective is to improve rider efficiency while maintaining a purely mechanical-hydraulic architecture.

---

# 1. Design Philosophy

The VELOX X-1 architecture is based upon a simple premise:

Human power is not always delivered at the moment maximum torque is required.

Examples:

* Hill climbing
* Standing starts
* Heavy cargo transport
* Urban stop-and-go cycling

The concept seeks to:

```text
Capture Energy
       вҶ“
Store Energy
       вҶ“
Release Energy
       вҶ“
Assist Rotation
```

